    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 2002 BMW M3 (E46) is a superlative example of naturally aspirated precision. The S54 3.2L inline-six engine features a high-pressure dual-VANOS system and individual throttle bodies, providing immediate throttle response and a linear climb to its 8,000 RPM redline. Power is managed via a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a variable M-differential lock. This collector-grade unit has undergone proactive subframe reinforcement and rod bearing service. The chassis dynamics are preserved by factory-spec dampers and bushings, ensuring the legendary 50/50 weight distribution remains communicative. The exterior retains its original luster with zero paint depth inconsistencies, while the Nappa leather interior shows no bolster compression or wear. Mechanically turn-key and cosmetically flawless.",
